ğŸ“ Start with the Purpose, Not the Process The goal of a stand-up is to synchronize the team, not to recite status updates. Focus on collaboration, shared accountability, and removing blockers.
ğŸ“ Keep It Dynamic and Interactive Standing in a circle and repeating the same format can lead to disengagement. Encourage team members to address challenges directly and brainstorm solutions. Rotate facilitation to keep it fresh.
ğŸ“ Limit Updates to What Matters Updates should focus on what was accomplished, whatâ€™s next, and whatâ€™s in the way. Avoid going into unnecessary details that derail the meetingâ€™s purpose.

